covidLtcNotes.notes:
Georgia reports long-term care data for Nursing Homes, Assisted Living Facilities, and Personal Care Homes with 25 beds or more. Data from Assisted Living Facilities and Personal Care Homes are reported together and categorized by CTP as Other and data from Nursing Homes is reported separately. 

Georgia reports cumulative data, but does not specify when cumulative reporting began. Resident and staff cases and deaths are reported separately. Data is updated daily. 

June 4, 2020: Deaths in the Other category decreased from June 1, 2020. 

October 22, 2020: Georgia reported number of Nursing Home facilities decreased by 3. Their reported number of Personal Care Homes decreased by 4. Personal Care Home staff cases decreased by 6. 

December 10, 2020: Georgia reported number of Nursing Home facilities decreased by 3.

December 31, 2020: Georgia reported cumulative  Nursing Home  COVID-19 positive residents decreased by 33. 

January 7, 2021: Cumulative number of Nursing Homes with an outbreak decreased by one. 

January 21, 2021: Cumulative number of Nursing Homes with an outbreak decreased by two. 

February 11, 2021: Other resident positives decreased by 14 and number of facilities decreased by 4.

February 25, 2021: Cumulative nursing homes affected dropped by 2. Cumulative nursing home resident positive dropped by over 139. Cumulative Other facilities affected dropped by 5. Cumulative Other resident positived dropped by 1. Cumulative Other staff positives dropped by 35.

March 4, 2021: Nursing homes facilities dropped by 1, nursing homes resident deaths dropped by 2, other facilities dropped by 4, and other resident positives dropped by 8.
